Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
changeIoConstraints(25.10)                          changeIoConstraints(25.10)

Name
       changeIoConstraints  - Changes the constraints of an I/O row defined in
       the I/O constraint file

Syntax
        changeIoConstraints

       [-help]

       [-forceIt]

       [-ioOrder {clockwise | counterclockwise | default} | -row <string>]

       [-spacing <num> | -removeSpacing]

       [-endSpace <num> | -removeEndSpace]

       [-firstCellSpacing <float>| -removeFirstCellSpacing]

       [-removeAll]

       Changes the constraints of an I/O row defined  in  the  I/O  constraint
       file.  If you do not specify the name of the I/O row, the command modi-
       fies all the I/O rows. You can use this command to move a IO pad .

Parameters
       -endSpace <num>
              Specifies the space, in <mu>meters, between the corner  pad  and
              the last I/O pad for the specified side of the row.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: float, optional

       -firstCellSpacing <float>
              Specifies  the  distance,  in <mu>meters, from the first cell to
              the beginning of the I/O row, based on the I/O order.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -forceIt
              Forces the I/O constraints to run on a non I/O row flow.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each changeIoConstraints parameter. For a detailed
              description

              of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command:

              man changeIoConstraints.

       -ioOrder {clockwise | counterclockwise | default}
              Changes the I/O placement order on all the rows.

              Note: This parameter is ignored if you specify a row name.

              Default: default

              Data_type: string, optional

       -removeAll
              Removes  all  the existing constraints on the I/O's. Evenly dis-
              tributes all the I/O's in the rows.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -removeEndSpace
              Removes the end space of the row.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -removeFirstCellSpacing
              Removes the spacing of the first cell.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -removeSpacing
              Remove the spacing constraint from I/O cells on a row.

       -row <string>
              Specifies the name of the row to modify the I/O constraints.

              Default: 1

              Data_type: string, optional

       -spacing <num>
              Specifies the global spacing, in <mu>meters, for all  the  I/O's
              on a row.

              Note:  changeIoConstraints -ioOrder -spacing <num> does not mod-
              ify the spacing of corner I/O pads.

              Default: 0

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
              * The following command removes the spacing constraint from  all
                I/O rows defined in the I/O constraint file:

                changeIoConstraints -removeSpacing

